description:
&lt;p&gt;If you are nurse or allied health professional with experience in care planning and co-ordination of care for a patients with long term conditions including MND patients and you have an interest in this specialist area, we want to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;MND Co-ordinator will work autonomously, but will require to collaborate closely with a wider teams such as MND Association, rehabilitation team, Palliative Care team, Speech and Language therapy team and neuro- centres in Bart&#39;s Health and BHRUT hospitals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;MND Co-Ordinator will work as part of the integrated services in Redbridge, collaborating with wide range of professionals such as nurses, social workers, occupational therapist.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Diagnosis of MND affect people physical and mental wellbeing as well as their families. You will be making a difference to people lives as a 1st port of contact for care planning, care co-ordination and support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;MND Co-ordinator role offer 18.45 hours of work; we welcome applicants who would like to job share with other position.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be subject to 6 months probation during which you will be equipped with relevant support in form of induction, supervision, training, shadowing, networking and admin support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For informal discussion, please contact Renata Wojciechowska, Integrated Team Manager on 07730618264.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;renata.wojciechowska@nelft.nhs.uk&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Probationary Period&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post will be subject to a probationary period. Internal applicants are exempt from the probationary period (unless you are an internal applicant currently part way through a probationary period or currently a bank member of staff).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Priority Post – Assessment/Interview info&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At NELFT we set very high standards to ensure we provide quality services. We require prospective employees to carry out an online literacy and numeracy test, equivalent to NVQ Level 2. For more information regarding our assessments, please visit our website. If you are shortlisted, invited for interview and successfully offered the post, you will be required to undertake an assessment for these skills during the pre-employment checks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;High Cost Area Supplement - London&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post also attracts payment for High Cost Area Supplement of 15% of the basic salary (with a minimum of £3,722 to a maximum of £4,743).&lt;/p&gt;
